        "timestamp": 1773216350,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Ukraine sends drone experts to Gulf, viewing an ‘opportunity’ Europe Issued on: 11/03/2026 - 09:05 Modified: 11/03/2026 - 09:06 Ukraine has sent drone expert teams to several Gulf countries to help in their fight against Iran's drones. The Ukrainian military has experience downing Iranian Shahed drones and the government “sees this as an opportunity,” explains FRANCE 24’s Gulliver Cragg, reporting from Kyiv. With the war against Russia still raging, Ukraine can position itself as a “high-tech arms producer that can bring in huge amounts of money,” notes Cragg. Modern wars grow interconnected as Ukraine and Russia seek strategic foothold in Iran war 11/03/2026 Middle East Oil shortage, not removal of sanctions, will boost Russia's energy exports, expert says 10/03/2026 Europe Iran war stifles Hormuz shipping: ‘Unprecedented’ impact on oil & global economy 10/03/2026 Middle East Europe showing it is 'prepared but does not want to be dragged into a war it wasn't consulted on' 09/03/2026 Europe Jailed Istanbul mayor goes on trial in corruption case slammed as political 09/03/2026 Europe 'This is all about defence': Macron addresses European security in Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Replay: Emmanuel Macron addresses Iran threat to EU member Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Europe rallies around Cyprus after Iranian strikes 09/03/2026 Europe Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East"
